David Bollier:

"There are a wide variety of software platforms that are experimenting with better ways to facilitate group deliberations and decision-making.  These programs t could have important implications for new types of governance.  The more notable experiments include [[Loomio]], [http://www.loomio.org] [[Democracy OS]] [http://democracyos.org] and [[Liquid Feedback]].  [http://liquidfeedback.org]  

The point of such systems is to enable direct, sustained and somewhat complicated discussions that can then clarify group sentiment and foster commitments that participants see as legitimate and meaningful."

